Class PackagePath

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.path.Path<String>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.path.StringPath
com.telenav.kivakit.resource.ResourcePath
com.telenav.kivakit.resource.packages.PackagePath
All Implemented Interfaces:
Sized, DoubleQuantizable, Quantizable, Stringable, StringSource, ResourcePathed, UriIdentified, Comparable<Path<String>>, Iterable<String>
public final class PackagePath extends ResourcePath
A ResourcePath to a Package.

Parsing

  • isPackagePath(String) - True if the given string can be parsed as a package path
  • parsePackagePath(Listener listener, String) - The specified package path, separated by either '/' or '.'
  • parsePackagePath(Listener listener, Class, String) - The specified package path, relative to the given class and separated by either '/' or '.'

Factories

  • packagePath(StringPath) - The specified package path
  • packagePath(Class) - The package where the given class resides
  • packagePath(Class, StringPath) - The specified path relative to the given class

Examples

 PackagePath.of(MyClass.class)
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath(MyClass.class, "resources/images")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath(MyClass.class, "resources.images")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath(getClass(), "resources/images")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath("com.telenav.kivakit/core")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath("com.telenav.kivakit.core")

      Returns:
      The sub-path of this path starting at given start index (inclusive) and extending to the end index (exclusive). If start and end are equal, the empty path is returned. If start and end are not equal and the path is absolute, the sub-path will still be absolute with the same root. If the start and end indexes are invalid, null is returned.
